Package: Blankman
Title: Statistical Tools for Friedman Test Analysis and Ranking Visualization
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Holden", "Blank", email = "blankh@usf.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides tools for conducting the Friedman test, a non-parametric 
    statistical test used for detecting differences in treatments across multiple 
    test attempts. The package includes functions to run the test, process and 
    visualize the rankings, and generate interpretable outputs for further analysis. 
    Designed for researchers and data analysts working with repeated measures or 
    block designs in experimental settings.
Depends: R (>= 3.1.2)
Imports: 
    stats,
    ggplot2,
    dplyr,
    tidyr
License: CC0
LazyData: true
